 DQL: Data query language:

 -> most most powerfull concept od sql
 -> when we want to retrive records from the table we can use DQL command 
 
 1)select
 -----------------------------------------------------------
                                                1)select:
 -----------------------------------------------------------

 using of select command we can retrive different deffirent records with spacific condition wise

    syntax:
        select *from <tablename>
        e.g.
        select*from student;

    -> fetch spacific columns from table

        syntax:
            select field name,field name..... from <tablename>;
            e.g.
                select name,subject from student;
                {agar hum * lgate hai to vo pura dikhata hai par isme bas name or subject hi dikhaye ga}

                +---------+---------+
                | name    | subject |
                +---------+---------+
                | mustved | python  |
                | boss    | java    |
                | ccc     | php     |
                | ddd     | NULL    |
                +---------+---------+

    -> fetch specific data using of spacific conditio wise for condition we use where close

        syntax:
            select *from student where city="ahmedabad";
            +----+---------+-----------+-------+---------------------+---------+
            | id | name    | city      | score | created_at          | subject |
            +----+---------+-----------+-------+---------------------+---------+
            |  1 | mustved | Ahmedabad | 78.65 | 2026-03-09 17:00:01 | python  |
            |  4 | ddd     | ahmedabad | 65.67 | 2026-03-09 17:00:01 | NULL    |
            +----+---------+-----------+-------+---------------------+---------+

            or

            select name,subject,city from student where city="ahmedabad";
            
            +---------+---------+-----------+
            | name    | subject | city      |
            +---------+---------+-----------+
            | mustved | python  | Ahmedabad |
            | ddd     | NULL    | ahmedabad |
            +---------+---------+-----------+

(1) conditional operator:
        =,!=,>,<,<=,>=
(2) logical operator:
        and ,or,not
(3) membership operator:
        in,not in,between
(4) pattern matching operator:
        like,not like
(5) null operator:
        is null, is not null

